HEADWORD: Reparable
<hw>Rep"a*ra*ble</hw> <pr>(r?p"?-r?-b'l)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>reparabilis</ets>: cf. F. <ets>r⟦eacute⟧parable</ets>.]</ety>
<def>Capable of being repaired, restored to a sound or good state, or
made good; restorable; <as>as, a <ex>reparable</ex>
injury</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

